com.github.randomcodeorg.ppplugin.ppdefaults.logging

Class AbstractLoggingProcessor

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.github.randomcodeorg.ppplugin.ppdefaults.AbstractClassModificationProcessor
      • com.github.randomcodeorg.ppplugin.ppdefaults.logging.AbstractLoggingProcessor
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    com.github.randomcodeorg.ppplugin.PProcessor
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    InsertCaughtExceptionLogProcessor, InsertMethodCallLogProcessor

    public abstract class AbstractLoggingProcessor
extends AbstractClassModificationProcessor
    A processor that can be inherited to insert logging calls. One can/should override the methods of this processor to modify/customize the way the logger is called.
    Author:
    Marcel Singer

        Sets the LoggingCodeSource that will be used to create the necessary lines of code.

        Note: It is not longer recommended to override the methods of this class directly. Instead one might use this method to customized the logging process.
